    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-10-13T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-10-13T18:00:00-05:00" n="428"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d428">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 PW (Peace)/10–1347: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Acting Political Adviser in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sebald</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-10-13T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 13, 1947—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>403. For your <gloss target="#t_Info1">info</gloss> status of Jap peace treaty
                    discussions currently as follows:</p>
                <p>[Here follows summary of developments since July 11.]</p>
                <p>Dept will examine the situation in the light of Dr. Wang’s findings in the matter
                    of the attitude of Soviet and other govts.</p>
                <p>4. Dept will be course keep you informed of significant developments.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
